Current accepted name: 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FB85F0F8FAAEFC43" authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[1072,1361,973,997]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FB85F0F8FAEBFC43" box="[1072,1300,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Solanum ferrugineum</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C4BEE03892D9A70FCF1F0CCFBC0F97F" blockId="1.[807,1461,1017,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FCF1F0CCFBF2FBB7" box="[836,1037,1017,1041]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FCF1F0CCFBF2FBB7" box="[836,1037,1017,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Solanum ficifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has long been treated as a synonym of the widespread tropical weed 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FB34F72CFAE0FB97" authority="Sw." authorityName="Sw." box="[1153,1311,1049,1073]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="torvum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FB34F72CFB13FB96" box="[1153,1260,1049,1072]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. torvum</emphasis>
Sw.
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FADCF72DFCA1FBE9" author="Dunal, M. - F." journalOrPublisher="Montpellier" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" refId="ref4413" refString="Dunal, M. - F. 1813. Histoire naturelle, medicale et economique des Solanum et des genres qui ont ete confundus avec eux. Montpellier." title="Histoire naturelle, medicale et economique des Solanum et des genres qui ont ete confundus avec eux" type="book" year="1813">Dunal, 1813</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FCDCF702FC5FFBE9" author="Dunal, M. - F." box="[873,928,1079,1103]" editor="A. P. de Candolle" journalOrPublisher="V. Masson, Paris" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 690" part="13" refId="ref4442" refString="Dunal, M. - F. 1852. Solanaceae, pp. 1 - 690. In: A. P. de Candolle (ed.), Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 13 (1). V. Masson, Paris." title="Solanaceae" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis" year="1852">1852</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FC1FF702FBBCFBE9" author="Whalen, M. D." box="[938,1091,1079,1103]" journalOrPublisher="Gentes Herbarum" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" pagination="179 - 282" part="12" refId="ref5325" refString="Whalen, M. D. 1984. Conspectus of species groups in Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum. Gentes Herbarum 12: 179 - 282." title="Conspectus of species groups in Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum" type="journal article" year="1984">Whalen, 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FBFBF70DFB42FBE9" author="Nee, M." box="[1102,1213,1079,1103]" editor="Nee, M. &amp; D. E. Symon &amp; R. N. Lester &amp; J. P. Jessop" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, Richmond" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" pagination="285 - 333" refId="ref5109" refString="Nee, M. 1999. Synopsis of Solanum in the New World, pp. 285 - 333. In: Nee, M., D. E. Symon, R. N. Lester &amp; J. P. Jessop (eds.), Solanaceae IV. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, Richmond." title="Synopsis of Solanum in the New World" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Solanaceae IV" year="1999">Nee, 1999</bibRefCitation>
) but none of the material in MA identifiable with Ortega’s epithet corresponds to that species. It is possible that this synonymy was predicated on the type locality of Cuba cited by Gómez Ortega; seeds were said to have been sent by Mariano Espinosa, a Cuban resident and correspondent of Gómez Ortega’s who was in contact with but not part of the Sessé and Mociño expedition (
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FC9BF625FC20FA8E" author="McVaugh, R." box="[814,991,1296,1320]" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the University of Michigan Herbarium" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" pagination="97 - 195" part="11" refId="ref5038" refString="McVaugh, R. 1977. Botanical results of the Sesse and Mocino expedition (1787 - 1803) I. Summary of excursions and travels. Contributions from the University of Michigan Herbarium 11: 97 - 195." title="Botanical results of the Sesse and Mocino expedition (1787 - 1803) I. Summary of excursions and travels" type="journal article" year="1977">McVaugh, 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FC5FF625FB49FA8E" author="Blanco, P. &amp; M. A. Puig-Samper &amp; G. Zamudio &amp; M. Valero &amp; J. L. Maldonado" box="[1002,1206,1296,1320]" journalOrPublisher="Ediciones Doce Calles-CSIC, Aranjuez" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" refId="ref4167" refString="Blanco, P., M. A. Puig-Samper, G. Zamudio, M. Valero &amp; J. L. Maldonado. 2000. Exploracion botanica de las Islas de Barlovento: Cuba y Puerto Rico. Siglo XVIII. La obra de Martin de Sesse y Jose Estevez. Ediciones Doce Calles-CSIC, Aranjuez." title="Exploracion botanica de las Islas de Barlovento: Cuba y Puerto Rico. Siglo XVIII. La obra de Martin de Sesse y Jose Estevez" type="book" year="2000">Blanco &amp; al., 2000</bibRefCitation>
). All of the material annotated as 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FC29F61AFBE5FAE1" box="[924,1050,1327,1351]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FC29F61AFBE5FAE1" box="[924,1050,1327,1351]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. ficifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I have found at MA (with a single expection see below) corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FB2DF67BFACEFAC0" box="[1176,1329,1358,1382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FB2DF67BFACEFAC0" box="[1176,1329,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. ferrugineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species of western Mexico that does not occur on Cuba and that differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FCD7F6B9FC37FA05" box="[866,968,1420,1443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="torvum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FCD7F6B9FC37FA05" box="[866,968,1420,1443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. torvum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its deflexed fruiting pedicels and glandular stellate trichomes. It is possible that Espinosa received seeds of 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FCF2F6FFFC1AFA47" box="[839,997,1481,1505]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FCF2F6FFFC1AFA47" box="[839,997,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. ferrugineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sessé whilst the latter was in Cuba (1795-1798) and then sent them to Gómez Ortega without provenance, hence the assumption they were from a Cuban plant. Some support for this explanation can be found also in the case of 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FC1AF570FA93F9FB" authority="(Ortega) Krapovickas" authorityName="Krapovickas" baseAuthorityName="Ortega" box="[943,1388,1605,1629]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Malvella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leprosa">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FC1AF570FB97F9FB" box="[943,1128,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Malvella leprosa</emphasis>
(Ortega) Krapovickas
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FACBF570FC8DF9DA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
), a common Mexican species unknown from Cuba, that was originally described by Ortega based on plants grown from supposedly Cuban seeds sent by Espinosa (
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892D9A70FC9BF5F4FBCCF97F" author="Fuertes J. &amp; P. A. Fryxell" box="[814,1075,1728,1753]" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" pagination="345 - 354" part="42" refId="ref4511" refString="Fuertes J. &amp; P. A. Fryxell 1993. Types of names of New World Malvaceae of Lagasca, Ortega, and Sesse &amp; Mocino. Taxon 42: 345 - 354" title="Types of names of New World Malvaceae of Lagasca, Ortega, and Sesse &amp; Mocino" type="journal article" year="1993">Fuertes &amp; Fryxell, 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C4BEE03892D9A72FCF1F5D5FE63FD59" blockId="1.[807,1461,1017,2000]" lastBlockId="3.[115,770,187,1139]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
Four sheets annotated as 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FBD7F5D5FB1CF951" box="[1122,1251,1759,1783]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FBD7F5D5FB1CF951" box="[1122,1251,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. ficifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in the general herbarium at MA, all appear to have been prepared from plants grown in the garden. MA308539 bears a label “ 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FC84F409FBA5F8F2" authority="Ortega" authorityName="Ortega" box="[817,1114,1852,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">Solanum ficifolium Ortega</taxonomicName>
, ex horto 1803” in the hand of José Demetrio Rodriguez and has sinuate leaves and two small inflorescences; it was collected after the publication of 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892D9A70FC92F4ACFC57F817" box="[807,936,1945,1969]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">
<emphasis id="BE803211892D9A70FC92F4ACFC57F817" box="[807,936,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">S. ficifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and possibly could be from different plants to those seen by Ortega. MA 334586/4 is a mixed collection with three plant fragments and two labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FDF3F38EFF02FF54" authority="Ortega" authorityName="Ortega" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">Solanum ficifolium Ortega</taxonomicName>
” in hand of José Demetrio Rodriguez (?) and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FFC8F3CCFEA7FEB7" box="[125,344,249,273]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">Solanum ficifolium</taxonomicName>
[Lagasca hand]/ Ortega Decad [unknown hand]/Rl. Jardin de Madrid [pale brown unknown hand, see above]”. Of the three fragments on sheet two are referable to 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FF42F263FE2DFECB" authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[247,466,342,366]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892F9A72FF42F263FE6DFEC8" box="[247,402,342,366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. ferrugineum</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
, one with more or less sinuate leaves (in the upper L of the sheet) and the other with the characteristic deflexed fruiting pedicels of that species (lower right of the sheet); neither of these fragments have flowers. The third plant fragment is a tiny piece of what appears to be 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FFC6F2C4FF22FDAE" box="[115,221,497,520]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis id="BE803211892F9A72FFC6F2C4FF22FDAE" box="[115,221,497,520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. capense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. A sheet (MA 334586/2) labelled “ 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FDDBF2C5FEF0FD81" authority="Ortega" authorityName="Ortega" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">Solanum ficifolium Ortega</taxonomicName>
” in unknown hand consists of three fragments that are clearly referable to 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FE15F11AFDC3FDE0" box="[416,572,558,582]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892F9A72FE15F11AFDC3FDE0" box="[416,572,558,582]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. ferrugineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two have flowers and fruit on deflexed pedicels and the third only flowers. These fragments are from older plants with angular (not sinuate) leaves, in 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FEA5F1BEFE92FD05" box="[272,365,651,675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE803211892F9A72FEA5F1BEFE92FD05" box="[272,365,651,675]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Solanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
juvenile leaves are often repand and sinuate (
<bibRefCitation id="E86593F2892F9A72FF7AF19FFEBDFD64" author="Roe, K. E." box="[207,322,682,706]" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" pagination="381 - 385" part="2" refId="ref5169" refString="Roe, K. E. 1966. Juvenile forms in Solanum mitlense and S. blodgettii (Solanaceae) and their importance in taxonomy. Sida 2 (5): 381 - 385." title="Juvenile forms in Solanum mitlense and S. blodgettii (Solanaceae) and their importance in taxonomy" type="journal article" year="1966">Roe, 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Also filed as 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FE51F19FFD68FD64" authority="MA" authorityName="MA" box="[484,663,682,706]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ficifolium">
<emphasis id="BE803211892F9A72FE51F19FFD9BFD64" box="[484,612,682,706]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. ficifolium</emphasis>
MA
</taxonomicName>
334586/3 has a typed label stating “ex. Hort Matr 1803” and is a good specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4BF49580892F9A72FF4EF1DDFE6AFCA6" box="[251,405,744,768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineum">
<emphasis id="BE803211892F9A72FF4EF1DDFE6AFCA6" box="[251,405,744,768]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">S. ferrugineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
